review:
Game is a mindfuck and a ;_;
10/10 pls play

Update: It is not until two months later when I sat down and pondered back on this game that I realized how amazing it was. Its a very long but comfy game to play at night after a long shift of work, while either snuggled up in a heated blanket or relaxing by the fan/ac. The story goes at a slow pace, carefully giving detail to the background, the characters, and the dialogue along the way to form the world currently around you. You drift along with the characters as they try to find answers to the questions that haunt them, and you yourself end up making a few theories along the way. Finally, after hours of wandering along this sea of mysteries and confusion, everything drifts together at the end. It took 18.5 hours for me to beat it but I was a bit slower in going through the dialogue because I always ate dinner while playing, so it'll probably be faster for you. Game is just absolutely amazing if you don't mind the slow burn. Along with the mystery there were many scenes that had a warm feeling of adventure and nostalgia to them, which goes very well with the art. Warning though, game can be very emotional at times, especially during the end. If you ever need something to just relax with and forget about the troubles of everyday life for a bit, please consider giving this game a try. Now time for me to go back to my h.w
